examples.en: The accident could have been prevented.
These problems have prevented me from completing the work.
Bad weather prevented us from leaving.
We were prevented from entering the site.
It prevented anarchy from breaking bounds.
Weather conditions prevented them from attempting the jump.
The college removed rules that prevented women from enrolling.
The biggest tragedy here is that the accident could have easily been prevented.
Only the timely arrival of the police prevented the situation from becoming worse.
Army roadblocks prevented any further forward movement.
Chaos could be prevented only by clear-sighted leadership.
Manacles prevented the bear from roaming beyond a very small area.
His bad health has prevented him from being able to function effectively in recent weeks.
